## Ideas That Spread (Virus Engineering)

### The "30/30" Meme
> "I give Farrice 30 minutes per month. He gives me 30 days of content that sounds like me."

**Why It Spreads**:
- Specific numbers
- Clear value proposition
- Surprisingly simple
- Easy to retell

**Variation for Clients to Say**:
> "My LinkedIn is handled. 30 minutes a month. That's it."

### The "Voice Extraction" Concept
> "He doesn't write content FOR me. He extracts content FROM me."

**Why It Spreads**:
- New concept (curiosity)
- Distinction from alternatives
- Sounds technical/credible
- Creates questions

### The "Anti-Ghostwriter" Paradox
> "I hired a ghostwriter who hates ghostwriting."

**Why It Spreads**:
- Paradox creates intrigue
- Memorable contradiction
- Demands explanation
- Stands out

